<br>
<br>
If you lose aggro after using those skills while it is casting it will re aggro you if you are upright and aggroable..<br>
<br>
This means if  you fade while a mob is casting a nuke on you, when that nuke lands it re aggros...<br>
<br>
if you fd and lose aggro then stand up in time for the spell to land while you are standing... it aggros.<br>
<br>
If you fd and are fd'd mobs normally don;t aggro you, but if you fd and stay down when a spell lands on you.... it used to break it 100% and reaggro the caster.<br>
<br>
The stonewall aa allows a chance for a monk to remain fd'd and non aggroable when said spell lands.<br>
<br>
if a monk fd/stands and the spell lands while the monk is standing, stone wall doesn;t do anything, the mob reaggros like the monk used fade.<br>
<br>
Nothing new here.<br>
<br>
